msIdentifier.collection: Harry C. Cochran History of Business Collection

msContents.summary: This fifteenth-century Italian manuscript contains lists of merchandise brought into the city of Florence and the duties paid for those products at customs.

supportDesc.extent: i+38+i; 230 x 300 mm bound to 235 x 310 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in pen with modern foliation of blank leaves in pencil, upper right recto

layoutDesc.layout: Multiple columns of varying numbers of lines; four columns for amounts ruled in lead; written area varies

binding.p: Half vellum with green patterned paper covers and spine title Gabelle di Firenze printed in black
